  <label>(3)</label>
 </disp-formula> If, instead, molecular diagnostics have not been used, the insects (including 
 <italic>y</italic>
 <sub>0</sub> pathogen-bearing insects) are transferred to a healthy plant for a fixed period of inoculation access. The ensuing proportion of plants that become infected is then used as a proxy for acquisition success (cf. ‘indirect assay’, subsection “Overview of experimental setup”). In this case, 
 <italic>y</italic>
 <sub>0</sub> (cf. 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pcbi.1007724.e004">Eq 3</xref>) is, on the one hand, the initial condition for the IAP process, and on the other hand, it is a function of the duration of the AAP process. For clarity, henceforth we use the general notation 
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>A</italic>
 </sub> and 
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>I</italic>
