  <label>(6)</label>
 </disp-formula> Details of the analysis used are presented in 
 <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="pcbi.1007724.s003">S3 Appendix</xref>. In summary, acquisition and inoculation response curves differ only in that the acquisition period is variable in the latter but constant in the former (
 <italic>Y</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>A</italic>
 </sub> = 
 <italic>τ</italic>) vs 
 <italic>Y</italic>(
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>A</italic>
 </sub>) respectively) while inoculation period is constant in the latter (
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>I</italic>
 </sub> = 
 <italic>τ</italic>) but variable in the former (
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>I</italic>
 </sub>). The exception to this pattern occurs when molecular diagnostics have been used, in which case 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pcbi.1007724.e004">Eq 3</xref> holds instead of 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pcbi.1007724.e006">Eq 5</xref>.
